Problem : Given 2 strings, merge them in an alternate way, i.e. the final stringâ€™s first character is the first character of the first string, the second character of the final string is the first character of the second string and so on.

Example :

Input : string 1 :"geeks"
        string 2 :"forgeeks"
Output: "gfeoerkgseeks"


Solution:

s1 = input("enter your string name")
s2 = input("enter your string name")
result = " "
i=0
    while( i < len(s1) or i<len(s2):
       if i<len(s1):
         result+ =s1[i]
       if i<len(s2):
         result+ = s2[i]
         
       i+=1
      
    print(result)  
      
